---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
import ComparisonTable from "../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro";
---

<Article
  title="Best Catan Expansions Ranked: Which One Should You Buy First?"
  description="We break down every major Catan expansion by what it adds, who it's for, and whether it's worth the price."
  game="catan"
  gameTitle="Catan"
  category="Buying Guide"
  product="catan-resource-tokens"
  publishDate="2025-05-01"
>
  <p>
    Catan has more expansions than most games have editions. The question isn't
    whether to expand — it's which one to grab first.
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="For most groups: get the 5–6 Player Extension if you need more seats, otherwise go straight for Seafarers." />

  <!-- Expansion Cards -->
  <div class="my-8 space-y-6">

    <!-- #1 -->
    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-emerald-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">
        #1 PICK
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">👥</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">5–6 Player Extension</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">Best First Buy</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">More Players</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Low Complexity</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60 mb-3">
        Adds components for 5th and 6th players, plus extra hex tiles for a larger island.
        Introduces the "Special Building Phase" where all players can build between turns.
      </p>
      <InfoBox type="info" title="Who needs this?">
        If you regularly play with 5+ people, this is essential. If your game nights are consistently 3–4, skip it.
      </InfoBox>
    </div>

    <!-- #2 -->
    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-blue-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">
        #2 FAN FAVORITE
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">⛵</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Seafarers</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">The Natural Evolution</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Ships</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-yellow-50 text-yellow-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Gold Hexes</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-purple-50 text-purple-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Pirate</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Exploration</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60 mb-3">
        Ships work like roads but over water. Multi-island scenarios give you real exploration.
        The gold hex produces any resource, adding flexibility without complexity. Most experienced
        players consider Seafarers + base game to be the "real" Catan.
      </p>
      <InfoBox type="tip">
        This is the safest expansion purchase. If your group enjoys base Catan, Seafarers will be a hit.
      </InfoBox>
    </div>

    <!-- #3 -->
    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-amber-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">
        #3 FOR HARDCORE
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">⚔️</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Cities & Knights</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">The Strategy Expansion</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-red-50 text-red-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Barbarians</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-purple-50 text-purple-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Knights</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">City Improvements</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">90–120 min</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60 mb-3">
        Transforms Catan from a gateway game into a serious strategy game. Commodities, city improvement
        tracks, knights defending against barbarian invasions. Many more decisions per turn.
      </p>
      <InfoBox type="warning">
        If your table includes casual players, this might alienate them. Perfect for groups who feel the base game is too simple or too luck-dependent.
      </InfoBox>
    </div>

    <!-- #4 -->
    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🎪</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Traders & Barbarians</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">The Variety Pack</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">5 Mini-Scenarios</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Low Complexity</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Five independent mini-scenarios (Fishermen, Rivers, The Great Wall, Barbarian Attack, Traders & Barbarians).
        Each adds a different twist without overwhelming anyone. Great for families and mixed groups.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- #5 -->
    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🏴‍☠️</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Explorers & Pirates</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">The Adventure Expansion</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-purple-50 text-purple-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Missions</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Exploration</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Standalone</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Ships carry settlers and goods, with mission-based goals beyond reaching 10 VP. Doesn't combine
        with Seafarers or C&K — it's its own experience. Be aware setup time increases a lot.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Quick Decision Guide</h2>

  <ComparisonTable>
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="text-left p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">Your Situation</th>
          <th class="text-left p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">Buy This</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">Often have 5–6 players</td>
          <td class="p-3 font-semibold">5–6 Player Extension</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">Want "more Catan" with minimal complexity</td>
          <td class="p-3 font-semibold">Seafarers</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">Base game feels too light / too lucky</td>
          <td class="p-3 font-semibold">Cities & Knights</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">Want variety without commitment</td>
          <td class="p-3 font-semibold">Traders & Barbarians</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">Want adventure and exploration</td>
          <td class="p-3 font-semibold">Explorers & Pirates</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </ComparisonTable>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="The Gold Standard Combo">
    <strong>Seafarers + Cities & Knights</strong> is the best combination for experienced players. Multi-island exploration meets deep strategy. But expect 2+ hours per game and substantial setup.
  </InfoBox>
</Article>
